A woman and her child have been hit by a car on Regent Street in Yeoville on Friday afternoon. Netcare 911 spokesperson Nick Dollman said: “the driver lost control of the vehicle and crashed through a boundary wall and into the side of a school building. “A mother and child were walking outside the school when they were struck by the vehicle. “The woman and the child were treated at the scene by Netcare 911 and other paramedics,” he said. Dollman added that the 5-year-old boy sustained moderate to serious injuries including a fracture to one of his legs and the mom sustained relatively minor injuries. Fortunately, both were in a stable condition and were transported by ambulances to the hospital for further assessment and care. -TNA Reporter      